<subSubSection box="[151,685,439,466]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="113.[151,685,439,466]" box="[151,685,439,466]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,685,439,466]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,685,439,466]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Malloch" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[207,509,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Bromeloecia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="winnemana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,509,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Bromeloecia winnemana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="113" pageNumber="114" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="113.[151,1436,510,751]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,510,535]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species group is defined by the following characters: male S5 with dark sclerotized band arching across from side to side anteriorly; surstylus usually simple with few short scattered setulae; male hind tarsomeres 3, 4 and 5 usually with additional process(es), protuberance(s) or long seta(e) (Figs. 24.1â€“24.6); female cerci usually narrowly contiguous, long and slender with unmodified setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="113.[151,1436,510,751]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
This species group, known mostly from southern United States of America and Mexico, includes three described species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1983" box="[362,474,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Bromeloecia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seltzeri">
<emphasis box="[362,474,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">B. seltzeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1983" box="[488,642,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Bromeloecia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsiglossa">
<emphasis box="[488,642,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">B. tarsiglossa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Malloch" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[697,857,692,715]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Bromeloecia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="winnemana">
<emphasis box="[697,857,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">B. winnemana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and approximately 15 undescribed species. The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Malloch" baseAuthorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Bromeloecia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="winnemana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">B. winnemana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is treated as a single operational taxonomic unit here, and will be fully revised in a later paper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
